    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date>March 1849</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Sir yours of the inst. I duly received<lb/> with the package by the express&#44; Since writing<lb/> I have obtained another subscriber <persName>Isaac Leriner</persName><lb/> the persons you mention in your letter for me<lb/> to call on I have done so&#44; but they will not<lb/> subscribe. I shall endeavour to obtain as many<lb/> as I can but I am afraid that they will not<lb/> be many as the people of this city are very slow<lb/> in subscribing&#44; I think you had better send<lb/> say 20 or 25 numbers of the Vol 7 I will<lb/> give the first number away gratas &#38; call<lb/> on those that I give them to they may<lb/> some of them subscribe by so doing&#44; I have<lb/> received from <persName>Jacob Ezekiel</persName> the following books<lb/> which I have subject to your order</p>
			<p>Catechism 30&#44; <sic>Sprit</sic> of <sic>Judeasm</sic> 6&#44; Jewish faith 2&#44;<lb/> spelling book 5&#44; daily Prayers 3 vol&#44; Daily Prayer 3 sets<lb/> 2 paper 1 full bound&#44; school teacher assistant 1&#44;<lb/> discourses on the jewish religion 4 full bound&#44;<lb/> <sic>Pentatuech</sic> 2 sets full bound 1 set paper&#44; Occident<lb/> 59 No of Vol first from No 1 to 10&#44; 72 No of<lb/> vol third from No 1 to 12&#44; 83 No Vol 4 from<lb/> No 1 to 12&#44; 51 No Vol 5 No 1 to 12&#44; 43 No<lb/> Vol second No 1 to 12&#44; he says he has some<lb/> more sets of Books which he would</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>hand over to me in case you write to him you<lb/> can request him to give me all books &#38; other<lb/> articles belonging to you if you think proper to<lb/> do so&#44; I will attend to your business is it<lb/> should be attended to &#38; use all endeavours to<lb/> obtain subscribers I am in hopes to obtain<lb/> a goodly number of subscribers&#44; you will<lb/> please when you write to me write<lb/> more plain as I found it difficult<lb/> to make out your writing in hopes<lb/> that this will find you in the enjoyment<lb/> of good health I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Resptly</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">N Ezekiel</persName></p>
			<p>you will please let me know if you paid<lb/> for the package as the bill has been sent<lb/> to me &#38; I declined paying <sic>untill</sic> I hear<lb/> from you&#44; in case you prepaid send<lb/> the receipt to me <persName role="author">N Ezekiel</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>

          
